.TH "ata_msleep" 9 "ata_msleep" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_msleep \- ATA EH owner aware msleep
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ata_msleep
.BI "(struct ata_port *ap "  ","
.BI "unsigned int msecs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ap" 12
ATA port to attribute the sleep to
.IP "msecs" 12
duration to sleep in milliseconds

Sleeps \fImsecs\fP.  If the current task is owner of \fIap\fP's EH, the
ownership is released before going to sleep and reacquired
after the sleep is complete.  IOW, other ports sharing the
\fIap->host\fP will be allowed to own the EH while this task is
sleeping.

LOCKING:
Might sleep.
